Durban - A motor cyclist was killed in a collission on the KZN South Coast on Sunday evening, Netcare 911 confirmed. Spokesperson Shawn Herbst said paramedics responded around 17:18pm to reports of a collision on Seaslopes Avenue in Uvongo. "Reports from the scene indicate that a motorcycle and a car were involved in a collision. Paramedics assessed the scene and found that the motorcyclist, an adult male had sustained fatal injuries and was declared deceased on the scene. "Two patients from the car, both adult males, had sustained moderate injuries and were treated on scene before being transported by ambulance to hospital for further assessment." In another accident a pedestrian was killed on  N2 South bound, uMhlanga. According to Herbst reports from the scene indicate that an adult male was struck down by a light motor vehicle. "Paramedics assessed the scene and found that the pedestrian had sustained fatal injuries and was declared deceased on the scene." POST